    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/actor/credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted on the basis that the single test condition evaluated corresponds directly to the regulatory submission scenario and is supported by N=11 constructs across two independent laboratories. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion. Note: the ValidationResult supporting this decision was generated under model configuration ansys-mechanical-2024q3-build-2 (modelVersion 2024-q3-build-2), whereas the current model of record is 2026-q1-build-7. The assessment team considers the validation evidence applicable because the 2026 rebuild preserved the contact formulation and material model; however, formal re-validation against the current build has not been completed.",
